⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Epistle to Henry II
node N1 · N1 · ⟦The Epistle to Henry II:N1:454c8d⟧

WHO   — The Epistle to Henry II — the prophetic testament
WHAT  — A sweeping prophetic testament — a famously dense chronology of ages from the Creation forward, threaded with visions of wars, persecutions, floods, comets, and the rise and fall of churches and empires; the prose companion to the cryptic verse of the Centuries.
WHERE — N1 · Nostradamus  Framework inputs: Les Propheties (1555)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the verse alone could not carry the whole weight of the vision; because a king-dedication lent the prophecies the dignity and shelter of patronage; because to lay out a chronology of the ages was to claim the largest possible canvas for the divine fire — and to stay obscure enough that no age could call it false.
HOW   — By biblical chronology and judicial astrology woven together; by an almost impenetrable Renaissance prose — Latinate, allusive, looping back on its own dates — that resists any single reading and so survives every reading.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I wrote a chronicle of the ages and gave it to a king — in language no age can pin down, so every age can read itself within it.

